## 2. Jobs Displaced (Traditional Method Replacement)

**EXAMPLE:**
```
Agricultural Spraying:
- 8 Traditional crop duster pilots → UAV fleet (displaced/partial)
- 12 Ground applicator crews → precision drone spraying (mixed)
  - Note: Reduced crew size from 4 to 1 per operation
  - Net displaced: ~9 positions (36 workers → 12 pilots)

Manual Monitoring:
- 15 Field scouts → multispectral drone imaging (displaced)
- 6 Irrigation inspectors → automated sensor networks (displaced)

Conservation:
- Traditional methods often preserve some ground crew in 
  hybrid operations (3 retrained as UAV support)

Total Displaced: ~28-32 positions (before retraining)
Retrained: +3 moved to UAV operations
Net Displaced: ~25-29
```

